<@U3E300R6Z>  i think it would be much easier to start with the docker images that you can find here to start doing some experimentation: <https://hub.docker.com/u/ibmblockchain/>     .  Because I wasn't clear on your question in terms of block size nor do I know what all companies are doing, i do know that with the version 0.6 version, there are companies that at minimum have 250,000 blocks with 1000 transactions per block running in production.

<@U1RG7CHG9> I do not know of a formal comparison between Hyperledger-fabric and Corda.  There also is version 0.6 and version 1.0 of Hyerpledger-fabric.  For Corda, they have published a whitepaper on line you could google.  For the version 1.0 for Hyperledger-fabric, you could look at the following: <https://wiki.hyperledger.org/community/fabric-design-docs>.
<@U3EF4NL01> I would suggest reaching out on the fabric-crypto channel to ask questions about confidentiality and encryption.
